            <title>[GROOVY-2057] MetaClassRegistryImpl creates mulitple Metaclasses for the same class </title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-2057</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If multiple Threads are requesting a Metaclass for the same class at the &quot;same&quot; time, multiple instances of the MetaClass will be created and intialized. This means a slow down for the Threads as well as requiring more memory (until the other MetaClasses are collected)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
